Oil Consumed by OPEC Members Rises 2.1% in June, Led by Kuwait

-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 
2011-08-17T17:19:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/oil-consumed-by-opec-members-rises-2-1-in-june-led-by-kuwait.html
Consumption of crude within OPEC
member nations rose 2.1 percent in June on higher use in  Kuwait ,
data supplied to the Joint Organization Data Initiative show.  Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries consumed 7.85
million barrels a day in June, compared with 7.69 million
barrels in May, data posted today on the  website  showed. The
association is supervised by the Riyadh-based  International
Energy Forum  and compiles data from primary sources.  The majority of the increase came from Kuwait, the group’s
fourth-largest producer. Its domestic USE rose 26 percent to
922,000 barrels a day from 730,000 barrels a month earlier, the
data showed.  Saudi Arabia , the group’s largest producer,
reported a 4.3 percent decrease in domestic crude oil
consumption to 1.89 million barrels a day.  The other members of OPEC are  Algeria , Angola, Iran, Iraq,
Ecuador, Libya, Nigeria, Qatar, Venezuela, and the United Arab
Emirates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
